      "question": "The roots of the quadratic equation $x^2 - 7x + 12 = 0$ are obtained by factorising the middle term. Which of the following is the correct pair of factors?",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Identify the quadratic equation: $x^2 - 7x + 12 = 0$.",
          "Find two numbers whose product is $12$ and sum is $-7$. These are $-3$ and $-4$.",
          "Split the middle term: $x^2 - 3x - 4x + 12 = 0$.",
          "Factor by grouping: $x(x - 3) - 4(x - 3) = 0$.",
          "The factors are $(x - 3)(x - 4) = 0$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$x^2 - 7x + 12 = 0 \\\\ x^2 - 3x - 4x + 12 = 0 \\\\ x(x - 3) - 4(x - 3) = 0 \\\\ (x - 3)(x - 4) = 0$"
      },
      "topic": "Quadratic Equations",
      "subtopic": "factorisation method",
      "marks": 1,
      "type": "mcq",
      "difficulty": "simple",
      "options": [
        "(A) $(x+3)(x+4)$",
        "(B) $(x-2)(x-6)$",
        "(C) $(x-3)(x-4)$",
        "(D) $(x+3)(x-4)$"
      ],
